defaultSirius Minerals is a UK-listed, global potash development company. The York Potash Project, a proposal to build a new state-of-the-art potash mine near Whitby in North Yorkshire, is the company’s flagship project. It has the potential to help Sirius to bec
defaultome a leading global potash producer, significantly boost the UK economy, and put the UK at the forefront of the global mining industry in the approach to innovative mine design in sensitive landscapes.
default&#xa0;
defaultSirius has defined the 
defaultworld’s
default largest highest and g
defaultrade polyhalite resource in North Yorkshire. Polyhalite is a rare form of potash which uniquely contains four of the six macro-nutrients necessary for plant growth. As the world’s population expands and the land available for farming diminishes, balanced a
defaultnd sustainable fertilization using poyhalite is rapidly becoming regarded as an effective solution to global food security.
