defaultThe extractives sector is central to the way we live our lives. Everything we see around us is made of materials that were either grown or mined. The places we live and work, how we travel, the tech
defaultnology we all rely upon, and the food we eat are all dependent on the extractives sector. As a result it is one of the oldest and largest industries in the world.
default&#xa0;
defaultExtractive industries make a significant contribution to the UK economy, both directly and t
defaulthrough supporting other key sectors such as construction, manufacturing, energy and agriculture. The value of the sector to the UK economy is estimated to be as much as £10 billion.
